text:
I know you are already talking about challenging yourself more with choreography for the next HoloFest, and I'm so hyped for that, but don't forget that you had enough dang challenges this time as it is! It was your first ever live 3D idol performance, the first time you actually had to learn choreography for the stage, to keep your cool, to do all of the behind the scenes prep and practice to get to the point where everything could come together and you could KILL IT on the day like you did. You had so many challenges to get here and to perform on the day, and you took all of them on - just remember to be proud of that before you start powering yourself up for Sharkcore on stage next year‚ñ°It'll be so amazing if you do your own choreography for next year, and you dancing in your room as a young shork is not cringe at all - to have that passion is something to be proud of. I'm proud of you!

I have gushed too much already under the members stream, so I will keep it brief here and say: I absolutely loved watching this, my first HoloFest, live to see you and Myth get your time in the sun you've been waiting for for so long. I am so looking forward to the day when I can be there in person and wave those penlights myself:_BlueLight::_gurapat::_RedLight:If Hololive does manage to wrangle together a world tour, then I'll see ya when you come to Europe; and if not, one day I will find a way to get myself to Japan for you and ENüíô
